--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages rdate.

The rdate utility retrieves the date and time from another machine on your
network, using the protocol described in RFC 868. If you run rdate as root, it
will set your machine's local time to the time of the machine that you queried.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: rdate
       rdate_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: rdate
       rdate_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  rdate_state
    Description: Control the state of the role.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Predetermined
    Type       : String
    Default    : 'install'
    Options    :
      Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
      Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'

